{"content":"---\ntitle: \"<faultPropagationQueries> of WCF\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nms.assetid: d85f66a7-e7b0-4dbb-83cc-89fa06fc9161\n---\n# \\<faultPropagationQueries> of WCF\n\nRepresents a collection of queries that are used to track the handling of faults that occur within an activity.  This event occurs each time a FaultHandler processes a fault. You should use such query to track the handling of faults that occur within an activity. The query is necessary for a  tracking participant to subscribe to fault propagation records.  \n  \nFor more information on tracking profile queries, see [Tracking Profiles](../../../../../docs/framework/windows-workflow-foundation/tracking-profiles.md).  \n  \n\\<system.serviceModel>  \n\\<tracking>  \n\\<profiles>  \n\\<trackingProfile>  \n\\<workflow>  \n\\<faultPropagationQueries>  \n  \n## Syntax  \n  \n```xml  \n<tracking>\n  <profiles>\n    <trackingProfile name=\"Name\">\n      <workflow>\n        <faultPropagationQueries>\n          <faultPropagationQuery faultSourceActivityName=\"String\"\n                                 faultHandlerActivityName=\"String\"/>\n        </faultPropagationQueries>\n      </workflow>\n    </trackingProfile>\n  </profiles>\n</tracking>\n```  \n  \n## Attributes and elements\n\nThe following sections describe attributes, child elements, and parent elements.\n  \n### Attributes\n\nNone.\n  \n### Child elements\n\n|Element|Description|  \n|-------------|-----------------|  \n|[\\<faultPropagationQuery>](faultpropagationquery-of-wcf.md)|A query that is used to track the handling of faults that occur within an activity.  This event occurs each time a FaultHandler processes a fault.|  \n  \n### Parent elements  \n  \n|Element|Description|  \n|-------------|-----------------|  \n|[\\<workflow>](../../../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/windows-workflow-foundation/workflow.md)|A configuration element that contains all queries for a specific workflow identified by the `activityDefinitionId` property.|  \n  \n## See also\n\n- <xref:System.ServiceModel.Activities.Tracking.Configuration.FaultPropagationQueryElementCollection?displayProperty=nameWithType>\n- <xref:System.Activities.Tracking.FaultPropagationQuery?displayProperty=nameWithType>\n- [Workflow Tracking and Tracing](../../../../../docs/framework/windows-workflow-foundation/workflow-tracking-and-tracing.md)\n- [Tracking Profiles](../../../../../docs/framework/windows-workflow-foundation/tracking-profiles.md)\n","nodes":[{"pos":[4,116],"embed":true,"restype":"x-metadata","content":"title: \"<faultPropagationQueries> of WCF\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nms.assetid: d85f66a7-e7b0-4dbb-83cc-89fa06fc9161","nodes":[{"content":"<faultPropagationQueries> of WCF","nodes":[{"pos":[0,32],"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;faultPropagationQueries&gt;</ph> of WCF","source":"<faultPropagationQueries> of WCF"}],"path":["title"],"nosxs":false}],"yml":true},{"pos":[123,156],"content":"\\<faultPropagationQueries> of WCF","linkify":"\\<faultPropagationQueries> of WCF","nodes":[{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">\\&lt;</ph>faultPropagationQueries&gt; of WCF","pos":[0,33],"source":"\\<faultPropagationQueries> of WCF"}]},{"content":"Represents a collection of queries that are used to track the handling of faults that occur within an activity.","pos":[158,269]},{"content":"This event occurs each time a FaultHandler processes a fault.","pos":[271,332]},{"content":"You should use such query to track the handling of faults that occur within an activity.","pos":[333,421]},{"content":"The query is necessary for a  tracking participant to subscribe to fault propagation records.","pos":[422,515]},{"pos":[521,675],"content":"For more information on tracking profile queries, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Tracking Profiles<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../../../docs/framework/windows-workflow-foundation/tracking-profiles.md)</ept>.","source":"For more information on tracking profile queries, see [Tracking Profiles](../../../../../docs/framework/win